<p>A <b><a href="Compound_(linguistics)" title="Compound (linguistics)">compound</a></b> is a word composed of more than one <a href="Free_morpheme" title="Free morpheme" class="mw-redirect">free morpheme</a>.</p>
<p>English compounds may be classified in several ways, such as the <a href="Word_class" title="Word class" class="mw-redirect">word classes</a> or the <a href="Semantic" title="Semantic" class="mw-redirect">semantic</a> relationship of their components.</p>
